BANK OF AMERICA CANADA Bank of America Canada ( ) , was a wholly owned U.S. bank subsidiary , headquartered in Toronto , Ontario , Canada .
It was a Schedule II bank under the Canada Bank Act to accept deposits which may be eligible for deposit insurance provided by the Canada Deposit Insurance Corporation .
In 2001 , Bank of America Canada re - established itself as a branch of Bank of America , N.A. of Charlotte , NC .
Canada 's revised Bank Act had created a new schedule , Schedule III , for banks that are foreign bank branches of foreign institutions that have been authorized under the Bank Act to conduct commercial operations deemed banking in Canada .
These branches have certain restrictions under Canadian law .
MEMBERSHIP Section::::Membership .
Bank of America Canada is a member of the Canadian Bankers Association and Canadian Payments Association .
